tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE proteins (
    protein_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protein_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    protein_type VARCHAR(100),
    gene_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES genes(gene_id)
);

CREATE TABLE gene_protein_interaction (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    gene_id INT NOT NULL,
    protein_id INT NOT NULL,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES genes(gene_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES proteins(protein_id)
);

CREATE TABLE experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    gene_id INT NOT NULL,
    protein_id INT NOT NULL,
    interaction_id INT NOT NULL,
    experiment_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES genes(gene_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES proteins(protein_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (interaction_id) REFERENCES gene_protein_interaction(interaction_id)
);

CREATE TABLE GeneProteinInteractions (
 interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 gene_id INT,
 protein_id INT,
 interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
 interaction_description TEXT,
 FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES Genes(gene_id),
 FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES Proteins(protein_id)
);

CREATE TABLE GeneFunctions (
 function_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 gene_id INT,
 function_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
 function_description TEXT,
 FOREIGN KEY (gene_id) REFERENCES Genes(gene_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ProteinFunctions (
 function_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 protein_id INT,
 function_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
 function_description TEXT,
 FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES Proteins(protein_id)
);
